	(1, 'AB5D001B', 8, 3, 'Supply Chain Analysts (S&amp;OP) -REMOTE', 'Starting from AUD 14,560/Annum', 'Remote Staff', 'Teamire', '', 'simon.reddy@teamire.com', 'Hiring Manager', '(+61) 416-253-907', '2557', 'Sydney NSW', '5-7 Years', 'Responsible for executing data analytics that impact overall supply chain projects. Generate tools and content to build data functionality supporting Sales and Operations Planning (S&amp;OP) processes. Participates in S&amp;OP processes and standardization initiatives. \r\n\r\nMonitors Supply Chain metrics to identify gaps in current processes, improve service levels to internal and external customers, reduce waste, and improve the value chain efficiency.\r\n\r\n\r\nEssential Duties and Responsibilities include, but are not limited to, the following:\r\nâ€¢	Perform data analysis to design and build ways to consolidate data associated with the S&amp;OP process; provide oversight of systems that facilitate transfer of demand and production requirement information across Demand Planning, Supply Planning, Material Planning and S&amp;OP.\r\nâ€¢	Support S&amp;OP systems through the development of databases and/or utilization of data entry forms and reports (potentially combined with Excel based spreadsheets and charts) to:\r\nïƒ¼	Efficiently upload all planning information.\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	Build and/or interpret queries and reports to provide ready-to-use Excel &amp; PowerPoint friendly information from Microsoft Access or similar database.\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	Support the S&amp;OP team to incorporate these queries and reports into day-to-day planning, scheduling, monitoring and reporting needs.\r\nïƒ¼	Build ad-hoc queries and reports to gather and present information effectively to support resolution of urgent supply chain issues.\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	Design novel Excel models, tools and templates by leveraging advanced formulae and programming (VBA, SQL).\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	Develop analytics to identify and improve reporting efficiency.\r\nïƒ¼	Develop and administer SharePoint sites to allow access to the routine reports and ad hoc information requests for all the supply chain stakeholders.\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	Develop and track metrics to measure the timeliness, accuracy and integrity of data from stakeholders. Align across teams to improve reporting integrity.\r\n\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	Provide support and tool or subject matter expertise to develop additional databases / reports. Document user requirements associated with development.\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	Build front-end applications to SQL Server databases for end-user data entry and record management.\r\n\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	Create and maintain entity relationship diagrams, user guides, and other system documentation.\r\n\r\nKnowledge, Skills, and Abilities:\r\nïƒ¼	Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Access, Excel and SharePoint, ERP Systems and popular Forecasting Apps like Pipedrive, Insightly, Prosper Works CRM, Tubular, INTUENDI, Zoho CRM, Capsule, Salesloft, Adaptive Insights. \r\nïƒ¼	Ability to interpret complex data and communicate recommendations\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	Proficiency in VB/VBA, SQL, HTML, CSS, and one of: ASP.Net, PHP, or JSP.\r\nïƒ¼	C# and web development experience are a plus.\r\n\r\nEducation and Experience:\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	For Associate Supply Chain Analyst level â€“ BE/BS/BA in business or scientific discipline and 2+ years of relevant experience or equivalent combination of education and experience.\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	For Supply Chain Analyst level - BS/BA in business or scientific discipline and 2-5 years of relevant experience or equivalent combination of education and experience.\r\n\r\nïƒ¼	For Sr Supply Chain Analyst level â€“ BE/ BS/BA in business or scientific discipline and 5+ years of relevant experience or equivalent combination of education and experience.\r\n\r\n*Salary &amp; level will be determined based on skills and related experience.\r\n\r\nThis is an opportunity to join our select team that is already leading the way in FMCG, Engineering, Pharmaceutical/Biotech industries. Apply today and learn more about Teamireâ€™s unwavering commitment to supporting the Supply Chain Network.\r\n\r\n', '2018-07-12 20:20:18', '2018-08-31', '1', '0', '0', 'Simon', '11', '3', 'Sales &amp; Operations Analyst (S&amp;OP)'),
	(2, '36DEDFEA', 6, 3, 'Demand Planner / Analyst-REMOTE', 'Starting from', 'Remote Staff', 'Teamire', 'Starting from AUD15,600/Annum', 'simon.reddy@teamire.com', 'Hiring Manager', '(+61) 416-253-907', '2557', 'Sydney NSW', '5-7 Years', 'Reporting to the Demand Manager, our Remote Demand Planners are responsible for ensuring best practise in demand planning performance is delivered and forecast accuracy is continually improved working within the S&amp;OP process as part of the Demand Management Team.\r\n\r\nThe primary areas of responsibility will span across:\r\n\r\nâ€¢	Conducting monthly Demand Review meetings as part of the overall S&amp;OP process \r\nâ€¢	Gathering, analysing, interrogating and validating demand data.\r\n\r\nâ€¢	Working with Customers, Key Account Managers (KAMs) and Customer Service to ensure latest market intel is reflected in the demand system, and a rolling 18-month forecast is maintained.\r\n\r\nâ€¢	Maintaining &amp; updating DFUs (demand forecasting units) in the demand planning system. This includes ensuring that item life cycle changes (new items, phase out, discontinued items) are captured &amp; dealt with in a timely manner.\r\nâ€¢	Running, analysing &amp; providing reporting on demand history, demand plan and forecast accuracy\r\nâ€¢	Managing procedures for measuring, managing and reducing forecast error, including work on continuous improvement in the forecast feedback mechanism\r\nâ€¢	Ensuring that the forecasting cycle is completed within the S&amp;OP process timelines\r\n The right candidate will be or have:\r\nï¶	Demand Planning experience, or experience in relevant related Supply Chain disciplines.\r\nï¶	Enjoy working with systems and large data-sets in a highly analytical &amp; problem solving focused role.\r\nï¶	High attention to detail with the ability to quickly interpret, analyse &amp; action complex scenarios &amp; information inputs.\r\nï¶	Ability to build &amp; maintain strong relationships and communication channels 