	(16, 'What does Teamire do?  ', 'Teamire goes global and selects only the cream of the crop of Supply Chain workforce. Our subject matter experts are professionals carefully chosen for their excellence in Supply Chain Management. Besides having advanced level of knowledge and work experience, these experts are well sought after to take on challenging roles with multinational corporations across the globe. They are grouped together for team building and knowledge sharing in all facets of end-to-end Supply Chain Management. Every of these experts we have on board are trained and certified as Six Sigma Supply Chain Professionals. They are also certified as Project Management Professional (PMP) ready to take on assignments in Supply Chain at all levels.\r\n\r\nTeamire goes global and selects only the cream of the crop of Supply Chain workforce. Our subject matter experts are professionals carefully chosen for their excellence in Supply Chain Management. Besides having advanced level of knowledge and work experience, these experts are well sought after to take on challenging roles with multinational corporations across the globe. They are grouped together for team building and knowledge sharing in all facets of end-to-end Supply Chain Management. Every of these experts we have on board are trained and certified as Six Sigma Supply Chain Professionals. They are also certified as Project Management Professional (PMP) ready to take on assignments in Supply Chain at all levels.\r\n\r\nIn a nutshell, Teamire offers its clients beyond the office-based staffing solution for its contingent Supply Chain operation. Teamire makes it all possible for its clients to overcome the critical challenge that they face in their day-to-day operation. \r\n\r\nOur business strategy is well aligned to achieve the highest level of customer satisfaction. While going global has allowed us to pick the cream of the crop in talent acquisition for our clients, this talent integration strategy is also helping our clients remove barriers in our ability to learn from supply chain leaders in other parts of the world and become more proficient in how to conduct a great business. \r\n', NULL, '1530970417.png', '2018-07-07 05:11:20', '1'),
	(17, 'Teamires Buddy System ', 'Teamires Buddy System is a knowledge sharing platform for its experts. It is a uniquely designed team building and mentoring program which is developed to assist both our experts and the clients. As part of the Buddy System, Q &amp; A forums are formed.  This forum usually benefits its clients in reducing downtime while answering Supply Chain related queries. Teamires user knowledge combined with its unique Buddy System is known to answer all ERP and related system queries for businesses in all categories.\r\n\r\nOur Buddy System also complements our highly talented members in their respective fields who are made up of local &amp; distributed teams from across the globe. By leveraging on the exceptional skills of our highly sought professionals located across all seven continents, Teamire is able to support all size of businesses in seamlessly managing their Supply Chain Operations. \r\n\r\n', NULL, '1530970564.png', '2018-07-07 05:13:48', '1'),
	(18, 'What could you expect from Teamire? ', 'Teamire is more than just a solution when it comes to finding the right talent for your business. Our entry in the ever so demanding Supply Chain Management come as traditional hiring methods continue to deliver below par to find the right candidate in urgent need of overhaul. \r\n\r\nTo ensure our Clients are getting value for your money, Teamire has put together a very simple business plan for its clients which clearly explain the short &amp; long-term benefit of using our services. As industry experts, our expert team has solution for nearly every business wanting excellence in Supply Chain in their process.\r\n\r\nWhile there are several reasons why companies should look to take advantage of what Teamire offers its clients, there is no comparison for our own unique business model and we are extremely proud of it. \r\n\r\n', NULL, '1530958589.png', '2018-07-07 05:16:28', '1'),
	(19, 'Benefits from teaming up with Teamire ', 'In Australia, average cost of hiring someone in Supply Chain with benefits and taxes is estimated around $94k to a business owner. While for a multinational company this high cost of labour can easily be shielded and may not be so much an of issue, SMEs do not always have the same tax privileges. And therefore, where possible Teamire will support SMEs with a discounted labour hire rate to help boost their business and profit. \r\n\r\nBecause we have a huge databank of highly skilled Supply Chain Professionals on standby to cover almost any section of a clients operation, we see this option as a big advantage to Teamires client. We not only have the capacity to significantly reduce our clients hiring lead-time in finding a suitable replacement in contingent workforce, at Teamire we believe we can find a replacement much faster than any internal HR or employment agency could ever do. \r\n\r\nWhile there will be some minor system-based training needed to get a contractor up to speed with their work, most of our candidates are familiar with using popular ERP systems thus will likely come ready to work for you. Finding the right candidate and preparing them for and assignment is never an easy task. A lot of time and resource is spent interviewing and preparing candidates. A direct benefit to client is all pre-employment training and associated costs will be borne by Teamire. \r\nAt Teamire distributed team means quality candidate at a reduced cost thus substantial savings and value for money for our clients. \r\n  \r\n\r\n\r\n', NULL, '1530958773.png', '2018-07-07 05:19:32', '1'),
	(20, 'Systematic Remote Collaboration ', 'Once we know your complete ongoing requirements, either a \r\nProject Management Professional (PMP) or Business Integration Manager (BIM) will be assigned to meet you and your team with an execution plan. We can support your business by providing experienced quality staff in Supply Chain experts from Business Analysts, S&amp;OP model developers and Leads, Demand Planners / Forecasting, Procurement Professionals that will make a difference to how you do your contract negotiations with vendors, Purchasing Professionals, Supply Planning experts, master minds of Production &amp; Capacity Planning, warehousing, Transport &amp; Freight specialist can all be available within 48-72 hours to any of business partners. \r\n\r\nWe can also merge with your in-house Supply Chain team to overcome your immediate challenges. \r\n  \r\nOur in-house human resource team will promptly process the contractor agreement and run through employee induction program, which means while our clients continue to focus on their core businesses, Teamire will take care of all tedious on boarding tasks to mirror with our clientâ€™s business plans. ', NULL, '1530959462.png', '2018-07-07 05:21:37', '1'),
	(21, 'Remote Team Performance Management ', 'Every Teamire member assigned to a project / client are subject to performance appraisal through Teamires employee performance appraisal program. Teamires employee performance can easily be measured with purpose driven metrices to measure employee and team performance. Whilst we think our member performance reporting methodology is conclusive, clients can always request to include anything that they specifically want measured. These reports are then shared and discussed with client, candidate and Teamire staff on a weekly basis for productivity in performance. The frequency of the productivity performance meeting is subject to clients requirement. \r\n\r\nOnce a candidate is onboard, they are automatically assigned a functional manager who will be also responsible for bringing both the employee and the client up to speed on work plan, working hours, report structure, access to systems, security, OH&amp;S, daily, weekly/monthly tasks and reporting. \r\n', NULL, '1530959395.png', '2018-07-07 05:24:33', '1'),
	(22, 'Secured Data Handling ', 'Before starting an assignment, all members are subject to signing a non-disclosure and privacy agreement as part of their contractual obligation for maintaining data security.  Upon accessing a clients database and working under a clients direct leadership, respective candidates will always be Teamires responsibility for producing quality work, maintaining business ethics, data security, networking, attendance, OH&amp;S, Training and supervision.  \r\n\r\nTeamire supervises clients contracted staff free of charge while on assignment. Through real time screen sharing and collaboration tools our team member tracking systems are specifically designed to track and monitor our distributed team for performance during their working hours from any corner of globe.  ', NULL, '1530959334.png', '2018-07-07 05:27:38', '1'),
